==Western Apache==

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|[jòː]}}

===Etymology===

From Proto-Athabascan *''yu·ʔ''. 

Cognates: Navajo ''yoo’'', Chiricahua ''yoo'', Lipan ''yoo'', Plains Apache ''zhoo''.

===Noun===
'''yoo''', '''-yo’''' ''possessed form'' (e.g., '''shiyo’''' "my beads", '''biyo’''' "her/his/their beads")

#[[bead]], beads

The form '''yoo''' is occurs in the San Carlos varieties; '''yoo’''' occurs in White Mountain and Dilze’eh (Tonto).

